Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat&color=C2410C&labelColor=E5E7EB\"></picture></a></p>\n./forge/utility_scripts/library_stats.py:17:    \"\"\"Resolve the metadata-version directory that owns stats for a requested library version.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:129:            f\"- Previous library version test-only metadata entries: {previous_library_test_only_metadata_entries}\\n\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:139:This PR provides test fixes and new metadata for {new_coordinates}, addressing runtime java test failures caused by changes in the updated library version.\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:152:- Previous library version metadata entries: {previous_library_metadata_entries}\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:154:- Previous library version coverage percentage: {previous_library_coverage_percent}\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:212:        help=\"Maven coordinates Group:Artifact:Version for the current library version\",\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py:217:        help=\"Target library version which was fixed by the workflow\",\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:100:* `tested-versions`: An array of library versions verified to work with this specific metadata.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:106:* `default-for`: A Java-format regex used to match library versions if no exact match exists in `tested-versions` (e.g., `\"0\\\\.0\\\\..*\"`).\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:113:* `skipped-versions`: An array of objects (with `version` and `reason`) to explicitly exclude library versions known to be broken or incompatible.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:204:The location of the test code is determined by the library version being tested:\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:275:   * fully-tested (the library is fully tested for each released library version)\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:63:        \"concrete proof that the new library version no longer needs the removed \"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:188:        f\"addressing Native Image run failures caused by changes in the updated library version.\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:244:        help=\"Maven coordinates Group:Artifact:Version for the current library version\",\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:249:        help=\"Target library version which was fixed by the workflow\",\n./docs/support/index.html:428:          <p class=\"lede\">Enter Maven coordinates to see whether this repository already tests reachability metadata for that library version.</p>\n./docs/CI.md:38:- Verify new library version compatibility ([.github/workflows/verify-new-library-version-compatibility.yml](../.github/workflows/verify-new-library-version-compatibility.yml))\n./docs/CI.md:40:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_javac_fix.py:95:    \"\"\"Build a diff text between the current and new test directories for a library version.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_javac_fix.py:199:            f\"- Previous library version test-only metadata entries: {previous_library_test_only_metadata_entries}\\n\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_javac_fix.py:210:This PR provides test fixes and new metadata for {new_coordinates}, addressing compile java failures caused by changes in the updated library version.\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_javac_fix.py:223:- Previous library version metadata entries: {previous_library_metadata_entries}\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_javac_fix.py:225:- Previous library version coverage percentage: {previous_library_coverage_percent}\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_javac_fix.py:294:        help=\"Maven coordinates Group:Artifact:Version for the current library version\",\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_javac_fix.py:299:        help=\"Target library version which was fixed by the workflow\",\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:20:| **Community contributor** | Add support for a missing library or update an existing entry to a newer library version. | Files a \"library-new-request\" or \"update existing library\" issue; the automation picks it up, optionally guided by custom instructions the contributor supplies. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:44:- An artifact-level `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json` that records, per metadata version: tested library versions, allowed packages, source/test/documentation URLs, optional `requires`, `default-for`, `skipped-versions`, and `override` flags.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:85:2. **Fix `javac` failures** raised by a library version bump.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:86:3. **Fix native-image runtime failures** raised by a library version bump.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:99:| `library-unsupported-version` | Issue | Compatibility automation found a newer upstream library version that is not currently supported by the existing metadata and tests. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:205:- **FR-M-5** Each `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/` directory must include a valid `index.json` enumerating its metadata versions and tested library versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:206:- **FR-M-6** Exactly one entry in a non-empty `index.json` must carry `latest: true`. If a library version is not in `tested-versions`, the harness selects an entry by matching the optional `default-for` regex.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:211:- **FR-T-1** Every supported library version must have tests that exercise the library's reachable surface enough to fail when metadata is wrong or missing.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:213:- **FR-T-3** Tests must not pin to specific library versions or bypass the library's public API in ways that would mask metadata gaps. Scaffold-only tests are not acceptable.\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:893:    \"\"\"Format a comparison of stats between two library ver